case_body_condition: Not recognizable - Partial skeletal parts only
case_circumstances: Sheriff's Department was notified in the early afternoon of May 1, 1995 that bones had been discovered along a ditch in Section #36 of Condit Township. The bones were primarily located in a harvested corn field with some bones discovered near the drainage ditch. Bones were confirmed to be human skeletal remains by the Forensic Anthropologist. The skeletal remains were scattered over a large area presumably by wild animals. Clothing, hair, and jewelry were discovered in the same area.
case_head_hair: Straight Brown hair with slight reddish tint
fingerprints: Fingerprint information is currently not available
case_clothing_with_body: White "V"-collard, short sleeve blouse. The blouse was a size medium and had buttons down the center of the front and back. There was a pocket on the left side of the shirt and the label read "Huntington Ridge". A pair of sweatpants was discovered near the remains.
case_jewelry: Two rings were discovered near the remains. The first ring was a gold colored wedding band. The second ring was gold colored with a large green stone in the center surrounded by smaller empty circles which appear to be missing small individual stones.
dental: Dental information / charting is available and entered
documents: There are currently no documents available for this case.
